%I A278299 #68 Apr 01 2026 23:59:40
%S A278299 2,4,6,9,12,15,19,24,30,34,40,46,56,61,69,77,90,96,106
%N A278299 a(n) is the tile count of the smallest polyomino with an n-coloring such that every color is adjacent to every other distinct color at least once.
%C A278299 Only edge-to-edge adjacencies are considered.
%C A278299 The sequence is bounded above by A053439(n-1).
%C A278299 a(n) is bounded below by n * ceiling((n - 1)/4). This bound is achieved for n=2, n=6, and n=10.
%C A278299 From _Peter Exley_, Mar 22 2026: (Start)
%C A278299 Lower bound: a(n) >= max(floor((n^2+n+5)/4), n*ceiling((n-1)/4)). The first term (edge bound) counts minimum internal edges needed; the second (contact bound) counts minimum cells per color.
%C A278299 For n == 2 (mod 4), a(n) = n*ceiling((n-1)/4) (contact bound is tight). Proved for n = 2, 6, 10, 14, 18.
%C A278299 For n == 0 (mod 4) with n <= 16, a(n) = floor((n^2+n+5)/4) (edge bound is tight). Proved for n = 4, 8, 12, 16.
%C A278299 This sequence is the inverse of the achromatic number problem for grid subgraphs: a(n) = min |V(H)| over connected subgraphs H of the infinite grid with achromatic number psi(H) >= n.
%C A278299 a(13) improved from upper bound 47 to proved value 46, a(17) from 78 to 77. (End)
%C A278299 116 <= a(21) <= 117, a(22)=132, 139 <= a(23) <= 141, 151 <= a(24) <= 154, 163 <= a(25) <= 168, a(26)=182, 190 <= a(27) <= 195. - _Nels Buhrley_, Mar 28 2026
%H A278299 Peter Exley, <a href="https://github.com/pexley-math/oeis-A278299">Solver code, data, and figures</a>, GitHub.
%e A278299 Example: for n = 4, the following diagram gives a minimal polyomino of a(4) = 6 tiles:
%e A278299       +---+---+
%e A278299       | 1 | 4 |
%e A278299   +---+---+---+
%e A278299   | 4 | 3 | 2 |
%e A278299   +---+---+---+
%e A278299           | 1 |
%e A278299           +---+
%e A278299 Example: for n = 10, the following diagram gives a minimal polyomino of a(10) = 30 tiles. Note that redundant adjacencies, e.g., between 2 and 7, can exist in minimal diagrams.
%e A278299               +---+---+
%e A278299               | 8 | 6 |
%e A278299           +---+---+---+---+---+
%e A278299           | 3 | 2 | 5 | 9 | 4 |
%e A278299   +---+---+---+---+---+---+---+---+
